The paper deals with the analysis of achievable information rates for coded modulation schemes in fiber-optic communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of hard decision decoding is also a key aspect of the paper, which is relevant to network information theory (cs.NI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the design of binary and nonbinary codes, which is related to coding theory (cs.SI).
